



### Green Chile Rice
### Homesick Texan p. 277

* 2 poblanos
* 1 jalapeno, seeded, roughly chopped
* 2 cloves garlic
* 1/2 tsp ground cumin
* 1/4 cup cilantro
* 1 Tbsp lime juice
* 1 Tbsp lard / veg oil
* 1 cup uncooked rice
* 1.25 cups chicken broth
* salt to taste

* Roast the poblanos under broiler until blackened (~5 minutes per side)
* place poblanos in paper sack for 20 minutes
* rub skin off poblanos; seed and chop
* blend poblanos; add jalapeno, garlic, cumin, cilantro, lime juice, 1 Tbsp water; puree until thick paste

* heat lard in a heavy pot on medium-low heat
* saute rice for 30 seconds
* add poblano puree, cook for 1 more minute
* add broth, bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat
* salt to taste
